recipieName: Fried egg on toast with apple & yogurt
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Eggs, 1 large (1.8oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 1 slice(s), toasted (1.1oz)
  • Sriracha, 1 tsp(s), optional (0.2oz)
  • Apple, 1 small (5.3oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, ⅓ cup(s) (2.6oz)
recipeInstructions:
Heat the oil in a non-stick pan over medium heat. Once the oil is hot, crack the egg into the pan. Cook for 3 minutes, or until cooked to your liking.

Remove the egg from the pan and place on top of warm toasted bread. Drizzle over sriracha, if using.

Enjoy with a sliced apple dipped in yogurt.

recipieName: Double cheese quesadilla with vegetable sticks & banana
recipeIngredients:
• Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, 2½ tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Part-skim ricotta cheese, 3 tbsp(s) (1.6oz)
  • Whole-wheat tortilla, 1 tortilla(s) (1.4oz)
  • Tomato, 1 medium, whole, diced (4.3oz)
  • Lettuce, 1 cup(s), shredded (1.3oz)
  • Avocado, 2 tbsp(s) (1.1oz)
  • Vegetable sticks (carrot, celery, cucumber, bell pepper), 1 cup(s) (4oz)
  • Banana, 1 extra small (2.9oz)
recipeInstructions:
In a small bowl, combine cheddar cheese and ricotta. Spread over one half of the wrap. Top with tomato and fold in half.

Place into a sandwich press, or a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat. Toast until the cheese has melted and the tortilla is lightly golden.

Serve quesadilla with the lettuce and mashed avocado on top, and vegetable sticks on the side.

DESSERT: Enjoy a banana for dessert.

recipieName: Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables
recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 4 tsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • White onion, chopped, ⅔ cup(s) (3.7oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 1 tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Thyme, fresh, 2 tsp(s), 5 sprigs (0.1oz)
  • Eggplant, ¼ eggplant(s), unpeeled, chopped (4.8oz)
  • Red bell pepper, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.7oz)
  • Zucchini, 1 medium, diced (6.9oz)
  • Tomatoes, canned, 1 can(s) (6.7oz)
  • Lentils, canned, drained, 1 cup(s), rinsed (6.3oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Portabella mushrooms, 2 piece(s), whole (5.9oz)
  • Arugula, 4 cup(s) (2.8oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner. Store the remaining serving in an airtight container and refrigerate for later in the week.

Lentils with roast mushrooms & Mediterranean vegetables instructions

Preheat oven 400°F. Lightly grease a medium roasting pan.

Heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil in a medium non-stick skillet over medium heat. Add onion and garlic, cook stirring for 3 minutes until soft. Stir in the thyme, eggplant, bell pepper and zucchini. Cook stirring for 2 minutes. Add tomatoes and 1/3 cup of water. Bring to a simmer. Simmer for 3 to 4 minutes until ratatouille thickens slightly. Remove from the heat, stir in the lentils. Season to taste. Spoon into the roasting pan.

Nestle the mushrooms in the ratatouille. Roast for 15 minutes until mushrooms are just tender. Divide into two portions. Spoon remaining 2 teaspoons of oil over the arugula, toss to coat. Scatter the arugula over the mushrooms. Season to taste. Serve.

TIP: If you prefer, you can swap the lentils for 2 poached eggs and serve them on top of the mushrooms and ratatouille.
NutritionInfo: Calories271Total Fat11 g- Saturated Fat1.8 gCholesterol0 mgSodium439 mgTotal Carbohydrate35.4 g- Dietary Fiber8.1 g- Total Sugars14.1 g-- Added Sugars0 gProtein12.6 g

recipeIngredients:
• Old fashioned (rolled) oats, 2 cup(s) (5.6oz)
  • 1% milk, 2 cup(s) (1pt)
  • Pear, 1 small, shredded (5.2oz)
  • Ground nutmeg, 1½ tsp(s) (0.1oz)
  • Non-fat plain Greek yogurt, 2 cup(s) (16oz)
  • Walnuts, 20 walnut(s), chopped (1.4oz)
  • Sesame seeds, 2 tbsp(s) (0.6oz)
  • Frozen berries, any type, 2 cup(s), frozen or fresh (13.9oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Overnight oats with berries & pear according to recipe instructions below. 

Portion into 4 separate containers or jars and refrigerate overnight so that you can grab and go in the morning.

When ready to eat, grab one container or jar. Spoon into a bowl, top with ½ cup berries and a quarter of the nut and seed mix. Sprinkle with a pinch of nutmeg if desired.

TIP: For cooler days, warm overnight oats in the microwave.

Overnight oats with berries & pear instructions

Place oats into a bowl or container. Add the milk, pear, nutmeg and yogurt. Stir to combine. Cover and place in the fridge overnight to soak.

To toast walnuts and sesame seeds, heat a small skillet over medium heat. Toast, stirring 2 to 3 minutes until golden being careful not to burn. Remove skillet from heat and allow to cool. Chop walnuts into small pieces. Store nut and seed mix in the fridge in a small airtight container.

When ready to eat, divide oat mixture between four bowls. Top each bowl with half a cup berries and a quarter of the toasted nut and seed mix. Sprinkle with a pinch of nutmeg if desired.

TIP: Prepared overnight oats mix will keep for 5 days in airtight containers in the fridge. Add remaining ingredients when ready to eat. For the nut mix, store in an airtight container in the fridge.
NutritionInfo: Calories420Total Fat13.5 g- Saturated Fat2.5 gCholesterol12 mgSodium99 mgTotal Carbohydrate55.2 g- Dietary Fiber8.9 g- Total Sugars19.7 g-- Added Sugars0 gProtein23.6 g

recipeIngredients:
• Red bell pepper, chopped, ⅔ cup(s) (3.5oz)
  • Zucchini, ½ medium, cut into ½ inch pieces (3.5oz)
  • Olive oil spray, 6 x two-second spray(s) (0.4oz)
  • Dried mixed herbs, 3 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Whole-wheat pita, 2 large pita(s) (6-1/2" dia) (4.5oz)
  • Tomato paste, 2 tbsp(s) (1.1oz)
  • Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, ⅔ cup(s) (2.6oz)
  • Basil, fresh, 8 leaf(s) (0.1oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es), to taste
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Roast vegetable pizza according to recipe instructions. Serve one pizza for lunch today and transfer remaining pizza to an airtight container and refrigerate for use later in the week.

Roasted vegetable pizza instructions

Preheat oven to 400°F. Arrange vegetables in a small roasting pan. Spray twice with oil then sprinkle over the dried mixed herbs, turn to coat. Roast for 10 to 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

Spray both sides of each pita with olive oil spray and place on a baking sheet. Spread tomato paste on pitas. Sprinkle each with half the shredded cheese. Top with roasted vegetables then sprinkle with remaining cheese.

Place baking sheet in the oven for 7 minutes until cheese has melted and pita pockets are warm. Sprinkle each with basil leaves. Season and serve.

TIP: The vegetables can be roasted up to 3 days ahead. Keep them in an airtight container in the fridge. If you're taking lunch to work, you can prepare the pizza to end of step 2, wrap in foil and warm in the microwave or in a sandwich press at work. If heating in a sandwich press place the pizza between tw sheets of parchment paper.
NutritionInfo: Calories372Total Fat14 g- Saturated Fat5.6 gCholesterol28 mgSodium592 mgTotal Carbohydrate44.8 g- Dietary Fiber7.1 g- Total Sugars7.4 g-- Added Sugars0 gProtein18.7 g

recipeIngredients:
• Extra virgin olive oil, 3 tsp(s) (0.5oz)
  • Cumin, ground, 3 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 3 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Beef top sirloin steak, any grade, very lean, 9 oz(s), cut into strips (9oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.9oz)
  • Red bell pepper, raw, 1 medium, sliced (4.2oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare Naked beef fajitas according to recipe instructions below.

Whilst preparing the meat, make salsa by mixing cucumber, tomato, cilantro, lime and pepper in a bowl and set aside.

Once the beef has cooked, place lettuce leaves on a serving plate and spoon one portion of the beef fajita mix inside topping with fresh salsa.

Fold romaine leaves and eat like a taco (be careful of spills!). Alternatively, shred lettuce leaves and enjoy as a salad.

TIP: Place remaining serves of the beef fajita recipe into two airtight containers and refrigerate for use later in the week.

Naked beef fajitas instructions

To make fajita seasoning, in a large bowl, combine olive oil with cumin, garlic and pepper. Add beef strips to bowl and massage seasoning into the strips.

Heat a large non-skillet skillet or wok over medium heat. Add onion and red pepper and cook, stirring until tender. Remove from pan and set aside.

Increase heat to high and add beef. Cook, stirring for 4 to 5 minutes or until browned. Return vegetables to pan and stir for a further 1 minute.

Remove from heat and divide the beef into three portions.

recipeIngredients:
• Eggs, 2 large (3.5oz)
  • Black pepper, 1 dash(es)
  • Baby spinach, 1 cup(s) (0.7oz)
  • Cheddar cheese, reduced-fat, shredded, 1 tbsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Whole-grain bread, 1 slice(s), toasted (1.1oz)
recipeInstructions:
Crack the eggs into a bowl, season with pepper and whisk. Stir in the baby spinach and cheddar cheese.

Heat the olive oil in a small non-stick skillet over medium heat and swirl to coat.

Pour in the egg mixture. Swirl the pan to evenly coat the base with the eggs. Using a spatula, lift the cooked egg and allow uncooked egg to flow underneath. Cook the egg mixture for about 3 minutes, until partially set. Flip with a spatula and cook for a further 2 to 3 minutes. Reduce heat to low, and continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes, or until done to your liking. 

Once cooked, fold omelet in half and serve with warm toast.

recipeIngredients:
• Honey, 1 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Soy sauce, low-sodium, 2 tsp(s) (0.3oz)
  • Garlic, minced, 2 tsp(s) (0.2oz)
  • Extra virgin olive oil, 5 tsp(s) (0.8oz)
  • Pork chop, sirloin, lean, bone-in, 9 oz(s), 2 x 4½ oz chops (9oz)
  • Mixed salad leaves, 2 cup(s) (3.3oz)
  • Tomato, 2 medium, whole, chopped (8.7oz)
  • Cucumber, 1 medium, sliced (7.1oz)
  • Red onion, chopped, ⅓ cup(s) (1.9oz)
  • Lemon, ½ medium (1.5oz)
recipeInstructions:
Prepare the Honey-glazed pork & salad according to recipe instructions below.

Enjoy one serving for dinner.

Store the remaining pork and undressed salad in separate airtight containers in the fridge to enjoy later in the week.

Honey-glazed pork & salad instructions

In a small bowl, combine honey, soy sauce, garlic and 4 teaspoons of water. 

Heat 2 teaspoons of oil in a non-stick skillet over medium-high heat and cook the pork for 2 to 3 minutes each side, until browned. Add the honey soy mixture, and continue to cook for a further 3 minutes, turning the pork half way. Transfer pork to a plate and cover with foil to rest.

Meanwhile, divide the mixed greens, tomato, cucumber, and onion between two serving plates. Season with pepper and drizzle over the remaining olive oil. Squeeze over lemon juice.

Serve the pork chops alongside the salad. Enjoy!
